Rebase Sky1 SMMUv3 ACPI boot-active bypass STE support for the Linux 7.1
CIX/Gentoo source state so it applies without fuzz.

Also include the small Sky1 PCIe ATS override support needed by the ACPI
bypass path.  The broader Sky1 miscellaneous patch that originally defined
ARM_SMMU_OPT_PCIE_ATS_OVERRIDE is not part of the 7.0 queue.

The ACPI Sky1 PCIe boot-bypass STEs and ATS override are opt-in so fixed
firmware can run the normal upstream path by default.  Boot defaults can be
provided with arm-smmu-v3.cix_sky1_pcie_boot_bypass=1,
arm-smmu-v3.cix_sky1_pcie_ats_override=1, or the convenience
arm-smmu-v3.cix_sky1_pcie_quirks=1 kernel command-line knob.

The same controls are also exposed as module parameters.  When a module
parameter is explicitly supplied, it overrides the corresponding kernel
command-line default; fine-grained module parameters can override individual
halves even when the convenience quirk default is set.  All controls remain
gated on the Sky1 PCIe SMMU hardware identity.

---

